Epigyne (Fig. 73
F-H
): broad, with a weakly sclerotized ventral plate (Fig. 73F). Scape wide, with lateral grooves (Fig. 73F). Copulatory openings separated approximately by the spermathecal diameter (Fig. 73
G-H
). Spermathecae partially visible at the sides of the scape through the semi-transparent tegument. Spermathecae small, globular, separated by about three diameters (Fig. 73H). Fertilization and copulatory ducts thin, long and distally coiled into two loops (Fig. 73H). Vulval pockets broad, sac-shaped, close to each others (Fig. 73H).
